# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Angel One SmartAPI credentials — COPY THIS FILE TO `.env` AND EDIT
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. cp .env.example .env
#   2. Edit .env with your real credentials (see README for how to get them)
#   3. Run: python3 tick_recorder.py
#
# The script auto-loads .env if it exists in the same directory.
# NEVER commit .env — it's already in .gitignore.
#
# HOW TO GET EACH VALUE:
#
#   ANGEL_API_KEY
#     1. Go to https://smartapi.angelbroking.com/
#     2. Log in with Angel One credentials
#     3. Click "Create App" → product type "Trading API"
#     4. Copy the API Key shown after creation
#
#   ANGEL_CLIENT_CODE
#     Your Angel One user ID (visible in your Angel profile).
#     Usually starts with a letter, e.g. A123456 or AA123456.
#
#   ANGEL_PIN
#     Your 4-digit TRADING PIN (used for order placement).
#     This is NOT your login password.
#
#   ANGEL_TOTP_SECRET
#     Base32 secret from Angel's TOTP setup page.
#     1. On smartapi.angelbroking.com, click "Generate TOTP"
#     2. When the QR code appears, click "Can't scan QR?"
#     3. The Base32 secret is shown (e.g. JBSWY3DPEHPK3PXPJBSWY3DPEHPK3PXP)
#     4. Paste that here.  ALSO scan the QR into Google Authenticator so
#        you can still login manually if needed.
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ANGEL_API_KEY=paste_your_smartapi_api_key_here
ANGEL_CLIENT_CODE=A123456
ANGEL_PIN=1234
ANGEL_TOTP_SECRET=JBSWY3DPEHPK3PXP
